<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:sy="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>Windows on k4i's blog</title><link>https://k4i.top/tags/windows/</link><description>Recent content in Windows on k4i's blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><managingEditor>sky_io@outlook.com (K4i)</managingEditor><webMaster>sky_io@outlook.com (K4i)</webMaster><copyright>All content is subject to the license of &lt;a rel="license noopener" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/" target="_blank"&gt;CC BY-NC-SA 4.0&lt;/a&gt; .</copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 17 Apr 2022 09:15:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://k4i.top/tags/windows/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Activate Windows With Your KMS Own Server</title><link>https://k4i.top/posts/activate-windows-with-your-own-kms-server/</link><pubDate>Sun, 17 Apr 2022 09:15:00 +0800</pubDate><author>sky_io@outlook.com (K4i)</author><atom:modified>Fri, 21 Oct 2022 08:59:20 +0800</atom:modified><guid>https://k4i.top/posts/activate-windows-with-your-own-kms-server/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;KMS&lt;sup id="fnref:1"&gt;&lt;a href="#fn:1" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; uses a client-server model, to use it, you need to have a KMS host (server) available on your network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Computers that activate with a KMS host need to have a specific product key (KMS client key, or formally as Microsoft Generic Volume License Key - GVLK).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Volume licensing editions are, by default, KMS clients with no extra configuration needed as the relevant GVLK is already there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="get-a-product-key"&gt;Get a product key&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Get a product key from &lt;a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/get-started/kms-client-activation-keys"&gt;kms client activation product keys&lt;/a&gt; for you running windows edition.&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator>K4i</dc:creator><media:content url="https://k4i.top//images/icons/windows-volume-licensing.png" medium="image"><media:title type="html">featured image</media:title></media:content><category>kms</category><category>windows</category><category>workspace-setup</category></item><item><title>Windows 11 VM with QEMU/KVM</title><link>https://k4i.top/posts/windows-11-vm-with-qemu-kvm/</link><pubDate>Sun, 10 Apr 2022 23:43:00 +0800</pubDate><author>sky_io@outlook.com (K4i)</author><atom:modified>Sat, 25 Mar 2023 23:17:59 +0800</atom:modified><guid>https://k4i.top/posts/windows-11-vm-with-qemu-kvm/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="get-a-windows-iso"&gt;Get a windows iso&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-in/software-download/windows11"&gt;MS: Download Windows 11&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="create-new-vm-with-virt-manager"&gt;Create new VM with virt-manager&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;open virt-manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;make sure you&amp;rsquo;ve connected to the QEMU/KVM (click the File option, then &amp;lsquo;Add Connection&amp;rsquo;, make sure hypervisor is selected to QEMU/KVM, and click connect)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;now QEMU/KVM will show up that you can add a vm to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src="https://k4i.top/images/posts/windows-11-vm-with-qemu-kvm/virt-manager-create-a-new-virtual-machine.png"
alt="Figure 1: create a new virtual machine with virt-manager"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
